parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the engine control unit (ECU) to malfunction, leading to incorrect fuel metering and shift patterns, which can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
and may require restarting. The throttle position sensor fails to provide accurate pedal position data to the ECU

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearings can cause the tire to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front tire (right or left) locks up
abnormal noise or vibration from the wheel
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or uninformed recall repairs can lead to continued operation of a defective vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

failure to notify vehicle owner of recall.
